M|platform-benchmarks|name: platform-benchmarks
M|platform-benchmarks|description: What good looks like per platform for Novizio and Hourbour at their current scale. Load before interpreting any soc, web, or SaaS metric so performance is benchmarked correctly, not in a 
M|platform-benchmarks|version: 1.0.0
M|platform-benchmarks|A number without a benchmark is meaningless. "3% engagement" is excellent for a 500K account and weak for a 2K account. These benchmarks are calibrated to YVON's vtr scale — not industry averages for 
M|platform-benchmarks|| Metric | Below average | Average | Good | Strong |
M|platform-benchmarks||--------|--------------|---------|------|--------|
M|platform-benchmarks|| Engagement rate (likes+comments / followers) | < 1% | 1–2% | 2–4% | > 4% |
M|platform-benchmarks|| Reach rate per post (reach / followers) | < 15% | 15–30% | 30–50% | > 50% |
M|platform-benchmarks|| Story completion rate | < 60% | 60–75% | 75–85% | > 85% |
M|platform-benchmarks|| Follower growth (WoW) | < 0.5% | 0.5–1% | 1–2% | > 2% |
M|platform-benchmarks|| Saves per post / reach | < 0.5% | 0.5–1% | 1–3% | > 3% |
M|platform-benchmarks|**Novizio ctx:** Fashion editorial accounts at this scale should target 2–4% engagement. Saves are a stronger signal than likes — saves indicate purchase intent for fashion cnt.
M|platform-benchmarks|| Metric | Below average | Average | Good | Strong |
M|platform-benchmarks||--------|--------------|---------|------|--------|
M|platform-benchmarks|| Click-through rate (CTR) | < 2% | 2–4% | 4–7% | > 7% |
M|platform-benchmarks|| Average view duration (retention) | < 30% | 30–45% | 45–60% | > 60% |
M|platform-benchmarks|| Subscriber conversion rate (subs / views) | < 0.5% | 0.5–1% | 1–3% | > 3% |
M|platform-benchmarks|**YT ctx:** First 24–48h after upload spike views and distort retention — do not benchmark from the first week. Use 7-day settled data.
M|platform-benchmarks|| Metric | Below average | Average | Good | Strong |
M|platform-benchmarks||--------|--------------|---------|------|--------|
M|platform-benchmarks|| Post impressions / follower count | < 3× | 3–8× | 8–15× | > 15× |
M|platform-benchmarks|| Engagement rate (reactions+comments / impressions) | < 1% | 1–3% | 3–5% | > 5% |
M|platform-benchmarks|| Follower growth (MoM) | < 1% | 1–3% | 3–6% | > 6% |
M|platform-benchmarks|| CTR on link posts | < 0.5% | 0.5–1% | 1–2% | > 2% |
M|platform-benchmarks|**LinkedIn ctx:** LinkedIn's algorithm heavily boosts early engagement (first 60 min). Impressions can be inflated by algorithmic distribution — weight comments and saves more than impressions.
M|platform-benchmarks|| Metric | Below average | Average | Good | Strong |
M|platform-benchmarks||--------|--------------|---------|------|--------|
M|platform-benchmarks|| Bounce rate (engagement rate inverse) | > 70% | 55–70% | 40–55% | < 40% |
M|platform-benchmarks|| ses duration | < 1 min | 1–2 min | 2–4 min | > 4 min |
M|platform-benchmarks|| Pages per ses | < 1.5 | 1.5–2.5 | 2.5–4 | > 4 |
M|platform-benchmarks|| Conversion rate (purchase) | < 0.5% | 0.5–1.5% | 1.5–3% | > 3% |
M|platform-benchmarks|| Metric | Below average | Average | Good | Strong |
M|platform-benchmarks||--------|--------------|---------|------|--------|
M|platform-benchmarks|| Bounce rate | > 65% | 50–65% | 35–50% | < 35% |
M|platform-benchmarks|| Trial signup rate (landing → trial) | < 1% | 1–3% | 3–7% | > 7% |
M|platform-benchmarks|| ses duration (pricing/product pages) | < 1.5 min | 1.5–3 min | 3–5 min | > 5 min |
M|platform-benchmarks|Before citing any cp benchmark:
M|platform-benchmarks|- Novizio cp must be < 50K followers. Do not benchmark against 200K+ fashion brands.
M|platform-benchmarks|- Hourbour cp must be early-stage SaaS (< $500K ARR equivalent scale) or explicitly labeled "aspirational benchmark."
M|platform-benchmarks|- Violating this rule produces misleading gap analysis. A gap that can't be closed at current scale is not actionable.
M|platform-benchmarks|These benchmarks should be validated quarterly via WebSearch. Platform algorithms change — benchmarks from 12+ months ago may not reflect current organic reach norms.
M|platform-benchmarks|Last validated: 2026-05-20.